the self-diffusion coefficients calculated using the standard MSD and eq. (6), D, and through
the iterative method, Dâˆ— . The data shown is an average of the calculations for coordinates
x and y, which have been analyzed separately after simulations. We also show the Îº values
obtained from the simulated data of the position of the disk to be compared with the input
data. This comparison between Îºo and Îº allows to understand the reach of the experimental-like
simulations, which are statistically limited, as it should be when measuring with a standard
video-microscopy set-up. The coefficient of diffusion values do not depend on the Îº value,
allowing to calculate an average value for D from the data of Table 1. The averages provide
